722372f.text:
Park Avenue, west side, between 92nd and 93rd Streets, showing 1160 and 1172 Park Avenue, newly built; 1160 replaces old Holland Court. The hotel down 92nd Street at the corner of Madison Avenue had only just taken the name Berkshire; in 1929, it was to change its name to Hotel Wales.
Autumn 1926.
John Adams Davis, Photogrepher.

722371f.text:
Park Avenue, south from end including 92nd Street.
Nos. 1155 Park Avenue (with awning), on the S. E. corner of 92nd Street, dates back to about 1913; but the other tall apartments
nearby are much newer.
The three nearest on the west side were built since 1925, No. 1135 on the S. E. corner of 91st Street about 1923, and the next
below it since 1925.
Widening of the Avenue at the expense of the parks will not take
place up here till 1929.
June 3, 1928
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

714826f-b.text:
